  <p>
    ISJ hosted a reading and phonics workshop for parents, sharing strategies, resources, and practical tips to support children's literacy development at home. The session was designed to strengthen the partnership between home and school, helping every child build strong foundations in reading with confidence.
  </p>

  <img src="/images/news/reading-phonics-inline.jpg" alt="Reading and phonics workshop at ISJ" class="img-wide" loading="lazy" />

  <p>
    Parents brought thoughtful questions and left with fresh ideas to encourage a love of reading at home. Workshops like these are a regular part of the ISJ calendar, reflecting the school's belief that literacy is built through consistent support both in the classroom and beyond it.
  </p>

